channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Claudia Sheinbaum projected to be Mexico's first woman president
item.description: Claudia Sheinbaum is projected to win Mexico's presidential election and become the first woman to lead the country's government, according to preliminary results. Follow here for the latest live news updates, results and more.

item.title: Mexico elects Claudia Sheinbaum, 1st woman to be president
item.description: Claudia Sheinbaum has been elected president of Mexico, marking the first time a woman has been chosen to lead the country, the election institute said.

item.title: Michael Doulas visits Israel to show solidarity as war in Gaza continues
item.description: Actor Michael Douglas paid a solidarity visit to an Israeli kibbutz that was hit hard in the Oct. 7 Hamas attack that sparked Israel's war against the Islamic militant group.

item.title: June 1, 2024 - Israel-Gaza news
item.description: President Joe Biden has laid out a three-phase proposal to end the conflict in Gaza, as global condemnation of Israel's offensive in Rafah grows.

item.title: 2 handguns, 35 shell casings recovered in fatal overnight shooting in Akron, Ohio
item.description: Authorities in Akron, Ohio, recovered two handguns and shell casings from a variety of weapons from the scene of an overnight shooting that left one dead and 25 injured.

item.description: Saturday's launch attempt of the long-awaited inaugural astronaut mission of Boeing's Starliner spacecraft was called off minutes before liftoff. Follow for our live updates.
